i looked back to all these letters people wrote to me in highschool and my journals i wrote to myself amd then i look at things from the herd at santafe.  it is so strange to see those two different people stairing back at me through the pages.  one saw me as a quote brooding, jaded, cold person" while the other )info i have gleened of people) as a inocent, happy-go-lucky person that brought life.  it is so wierd that i have been so many different people to so many... though i dont see myself as a phony or phake person.  the herd brought out the love in me.  really me favorite thing is to see people smile and laugh.  i really love to make people feel better to talk and to solve or to distract or to anything at all.   when i become the fuck you girl is when i dont feel anything at all and when i feel helpless to help

http://www.myfootprint.org/

above is a website that calculates the amount of acres you personally use per year.  I think everyone should take a look at it because it really puts how the little things add up and how that realates to our dwindling natural resources.  It gives good ideas on how to help as well, so its a good website!


Mine was 9 acres by the by lower than the avg 24 but i still need 2.1 planets! ouch!

another good weekend fo me.  hell all last week was good.  chris and i have been taking turns cooking and cleaning and it has brought us alot closer i think.  we also went to the beach on friday saw pirates, took stella to a dog park on sat and went out to play pool, and on sunday i went riding with stacy and out to dinner with her... i really don't want this not having school thing not to end.  i have worked more hard and long hours this past couple of months than ever but to able to come home and drop it is great. and i love all the people i work with and the work i do so it is very fufilling.... i hope everyone else is doing well as too... sorry if i havent talked to some of you in a while but i have been running my ass off :) weeeee just call me or poke me and stuff! love to all.

Once you are tagged you MUST write a blog about your 6 weird habits/things as well as state this rule clearly. In the end, you need to choose the next six people to be tagged and list their names.
ok ok ok lemme think...

1. i am terrified of closing umbrellas, so much in fact that I never use them and get soaked everytime it rains.
2. i absolutely despise the feel of velvet... it makes me sick to my stomach.
3. can't stand the squeak of stirofoam, snow, or sand
4. i composively die my hair whenever I am upset depressed etc..
5. i sing myself to sleep sometimes 
6. i am crazily non competitive and get really upset and worked up whith competitive people. It is hard to decribe. I go out of my way to avoid competitive situations and I am really anxious and gaurded around competitive people.  I guess it is my pet peeve when people constantly try to out due everyone else in trivial things.ahk! i am getting angry just thinking about it!

so i guess thats it off the top of my head nothing really cool i bet people that know me well could think of better ones. lets see i will tag... Jenny, Chris(Chris), Moogs, Erin, and Manda...
sorry if you guys were ALREADY tagged it just means now you are doublly tagged :)
